# CareerSwitchKit — environment variables
# Copy the values you have into .env.local for local dev, and set them in
# Vercel → Settings → Environment Variables for production.
# Everything here is NEXT_PUBLIC_* (safe to expose in the browser — these are
# public tracking IDs, not secrets). Leave a var blank to keep that script off.

# Google Analytics 4 measurement ID — analytics.google.com → Admin → Data streams.
# Defaults to the live property (G-VZTZ8KD05Z) baked into the code; set only to override.
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=

# Microsoft Clarity project ID — clarity.microsoft.com → your project → Settings → Setup.
# Defaults to the live project (x84g7j2y7p) baked into the code; set only to override.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLARITY_PROJECT_ID=

# Meta (Facebook) Pixel ID — business.facebook.com → Events Manager → your pixel.
# Defaults to the live pixel (2156940741754118) baked into the code; set only to override.
NEXT_PUBLIC_META_PIXEL_ID=
